We are familiar with the devastating cloudburst that hits the Himalayas every year, including the latest ones in Amarnath and Kullu this year.

While the Himalayas are prone to the moisture-rich air reaching up to them due to the faster warming up of oceans leading to cloudbursts, let us know more about them and how we can protect ourselves from this nature’s wrath, in this video of our TREK (The Road to Environmental Knowledge) video series.

Meet our youngest Eco-Warrior, Neev Agarwal!!

Our next feature of the ‘Humans of Trees’ series is an 8 year old green enthusiast @pathways.gurgaon @kanikaagarwal who is passionate about saving his environment and believes in the power of his voice to raise awareness for a good cause.

He proves that age has no bar when it comes to making a difference and serving the planet. And, he is not alone in thinking this way!

In fact, our younger generation is constantly following up with Climate Change and is well aware that tree plantation is one of the most practical solutions to combat the Climate Crisis and alarming levels of air pollution. 

Watch the video to know more about the thoughts of this budding environmentalist on deforestation and its consequences if we don’t act fast on restoring the lost balance on Earth by planting more trees!

A big thank you to YES Foundation for recognizing our partnership and to Simar Mann for representing us on this proud occasion. Let’s continue building a greener, brighter future together!

𝐀 𝐒𝐞𝐞𝐝 𝐨𝐟 𝐂𝐡𝐚𝐧𝐠𝐞, 𝐀 𝐅𝐮𝐭𝐮𝐫𝐞 𝐨𝐟 𝐆𝐫𝐨𝐰𝐭𝐡 

The joy of witnessing growth - whether it’s a child or a plant, is immeasurable. It reflects a sense of nurturing and contributes to a brighter, more sustainable tomorrow. 

On December 6, 2024, @trg_screen partnered with SankalpTaru to bring this emotion to life. 

At Government Higher Primary School, Nallurhalli, Whitefield, Bangalore, we planted 30 indoor plants, each carrying its own unique essence:

🌿 Areca Palm
🌿 Money Plant
🌿 Aloe Vera
🌿 Snake Plant
🌿 Rubber Plant
🌿 Indian Mint
🌿 Spider Plant
🌿 Petra
🌿 Dwarf Umbrella Plant

This activity wasn’t just about planting; it was about planting hope. TRG Screen captured this same spirit—not only in the hearts of their employees but also in the eager minds of these children, whose futures are now intertwined with the nurturing of life and the planet. 🌍💚

Through this planting activity, TRG Screen brought together their team, inspired the next generation, and contributed to a greener tomorrow.

We celebrate this impactful partnership with heartfelt gratitude and look forward to nurturing even more meaningful collaborations ahead!

Special thanks:
Event Manager: Tripti Trivedi from @zinnov.management.consulting
Program Coordinator: @_d_s_ouza_
Operations Coordinator: @arjunmramakrishna

latestPosts.caption:
𝗣𝗮𝗿𝘁 𝟮/𝗦𝗲𝗿𝗶𝗲𝘀: Why it matters:

1. Climate Protection: Energy conservation reduces greenhouse gas emissions, helping to combat climate change. 

2. Resource Efficiency: Conserve Energy to extend natural finite resources lifespan

3. Economic Benefits: Reduction in energy consumption lowers electricity bills and boosts industrial efficiency. 

4. Energy Security: Reduce dependence on imported fuels, strengthens self-reliance and energy stability. 

🌿 A small change today can make a big difference tomorrow! 🌱

#WhyEnergyMatters #EnergyConservationDay #SaveThePlanet #CarbonFootprint #EnergySavings #EcoWarrior #EnergySecurity #SustainabilityGoals #ClimateChangeAction #ConserveResources #ReduceEmissions #EnergyForFuture #IndiaClimateAction #CleanAndGreen #EcoConscious #EnergyForTomorrow #ActForClimate #SustainableGrowth #EnergyIsWealth

𝗣𝗮𝗿𝘁 𝟭/𝗦𝗲𝗿𝗶𝗲𝘀: National Energy Conservation Day(NECD) is observed annually on 14th December in India. It serves as a reminder of the crucial role energy plays in our lives and the urgent need to use it responsibly.

Initiated by the Bureau of Energy Efficiency (BEE) under the Ministry of Power, NECD is part of India’s larger goal for sustainable development and energy security.

The focus? Promoting energy efficiency, renewable energy adoption, and reducing reliance on finite resources.

With a goal: Energy saved is energy generated!
